@sbodenstein I submitted a PR #8603 which has some standalone op to fulfill partially this operator. 
It's still hard to estimate a timeframe for the rest stuffs, but pure gluon version SSD using custom blocks are now running pretty well in my experiments. And most of these blocks are reusable for YOLO, Faster-rcnn, Mask-RCNN, and so on.
An preview version for these will soon be available.

@KellenSunderland The crash will occur too if importing cv2 after mxnet with `gperftools`.
I set `USE_GPERFTOOLS = 0` and `USE_JEMALLOC = 0`. Rebuild mxnet without `gperftools`. There will be no crash.
`USE_GPERFTOOLS = 1` is the default setting. When the machine doesn't have `gperftools`, the building will not have `gperftools`.

@sbodenstein Functionally, yes, but not identical api. This one provide more options.
Do you have a suggestion for the name?
There's an alias "box_non_maximum_suppression"
